    <section class="projects" id="projects">
          <div class="about-project">
            <h1>Projects</h1>
              <div class="projects-grid">
                  <div class="project">
                      <h2>Smart Home Automation System</h2>
                      <p>Developed a smart home automation system using Arduino and various sensors to control home appliances.</p>
                      <ul>
                          <li><b>Lighting Control:</b> Automatic adjustment of lighting based on ambient light levels.</li>
                          <li><b>Temperature Regulation:</b> Automated control of heating and cooling systems using temperature sensors.</li>
                          <li><b>Security:</b> Integration of motion detectors and door sensors for enhanced home security.</li>
                          <li><b>Remote Access:</b> Controlled via a mobile app for remote monitoring and control.</li>
                      </ul>
                      <p><strong>Technologies Used:</strong> Arduino, IoT, Sensors (temperature, motion, light), Mobile App Development.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="project">
                      <h2>Real-Time Object Detection Using YOLOv8</h2>
                      <p>Implemented a real-time object detection system using YOLOv8 (You Only Look Once version 8).</p>
                      <ul>
                          <li><b>Dataset Preparation:</b> Collected and annotated a custom dataset for various objects.</li>
                          <li><b>Model Training:</b>Trained the YOLOv8 model using the annotated dataset.</li>
                          <li><b>Real-Time Detection:</b> Developed a Python application to perform real-time object detection using a webcam feed.</li>
                          <li><b>Performance Optimization:</b> Enhanced the model for faster processing and higher accuracy.</li>
                      </ul>
                      <p><strong>Technologies Used:</strong> Python, YOLOv8, OpenCV, Machine Learning.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="project">
                      <h2>Wireless Health Monitoring System</h2>
                      <p>Created a wireless health monitoring system to track vital signs such as heart rate and body temperature.</p>
                      <ul>
                          <li><b>Wearable Device:</b> A wearable sensor module to collect health data.</li>
                          <li><b>Data Transmission:</b> Wireless transmission of data to a central monitoring unit.</li>
                          <li><b>Data Analysis:</b> Real-time analysis and visualization of health metrics.</li>
                          <li><b>Alert System:</b> Automated alerts for abnormal readings sent to healthcare providers.</li>
                      </ul>
                      <p><strong>Technologies Used:</strong> Microcontroller (e.g., ESP8266), Wireless Communication, Sensors (heart rate, temperature), Data Visualization.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="project">
                      <h2>FPGA-Based Digital Signal Processing</h2>
                      <p>Designed and implemented digital signal processing (DSP) algorithms on an FPGA for real-time signal processing applications.</p>
                      <ul>
                          <li><b>Algorithm Design:</b> Developed DSP algorithms such as filters and FFT.</li>
                          <li><b>FPGA Implementation:</b> Used VHDL/Verilog to implement the algorithms on an FPGA board.</li>
                          <li><b>Performance Analysis:</b> Evaluated the performance of the FPGA-based implementation compared to software-based solutions.</li>
                          <li><b>Application:</b> Applied the system to process audio signals in real-time.</li>
                      </ul>
                      <p><strong>Technologies Used:</strong> FPGA (e.g., Xilinx, Altera), VHDL/Verilog, Digital Signal Processing, MATLAB.</p>
                  </div>
              </div>
          </div>

